I wanna make a thread on my knowledge of League of Legend lol not sure if im autistic enough... will win me some normie cred tho

The dark day has come. It is time for me to do the unthinkable, to make a twitter thread on a "vidya": League of Legends, the 21st century version of chess.

Unknown strategies, forgotten facts, and insights - from my 9 years of playing this blessed/accursed game.

Thred.

I am probably one of the people with the most diverse League experience ever.

I have played duo with the lowest ranked person in EU West and gone 0/7 against a Bronze V Pantheon.

I have taken a shit on Challenger tournament pro-players on their mains.

All with my trusty Udyr.

The proper way to play - pick one champion and play nothing else. Not just "main", but literally play no other champions.

Otherwise you're never going to experience the real game.

If you play different champions, the game gets more boring with time. With one, it's the opposite.

It takes around three months to get the basic workings, but after that it gets closer to speedrunning, with min-maxing every move and auto-attack.

I would suggest never buying items that add more complexity - like Hydra, other active items etc. It's complicated enough as it is.

The "meta" is of course a meme and almost never actually matters. Many turboautists have climbed the ranks of Korea and all other regions by playing a "homebrew" build and just focusing on getting incredibly good with their champion and learning how it functions.

The only good "trick" for League is that the easiest way to win is to get your opponents mad.

Mock them in the chat, the "?" is one of the most effective ones. Point the name of a specific player and "thank" him. In no time the entire opponent time will start crying in all-chat.

Now, for some forgotten facts.

There existed a rumor, that when you go to really low elo, like REALLY low, there's a secret community of players there called "Elo China" (from the digging so deep you end up in China TV trope). They were there on purpose to play with each other.

Back in the day, League could be hacked using Cheat Engine on your masteries, allowing you to have a zero second cooldown infinite flash. A few people abused it, but it got fixed very quickly, so only a few videos of it exist online.
Honestly? An absolute king, this mfer played the system, turned the game around, gotta put some respect on his name

A relatively widely-known one: there was made an alternative map for League, 5vs5 - thankfully it was not released, or otherwise it most likely would have killed the game by splitting the fanbase in two and making balancing impossible.

Still, I think - what it could have been...
